      <string>This game requires 2 players.
The board is a 7x7 grid which the 2 players make their moves.

The rules for the game are as follows:
- A player can only move in diagonals or cardinal directions (North, South, East, West).
- When a player is not moving (i.e. it is the opponentâ€™s turn to move), 
  an invisible shooting zone is assumed in the diagonals and cardinal lines.
- If the opponent chooses to make his move to the position where these lines lie, he loses and the game ends. 
  So each player must move to a square where the opponent cannot shoot him.
- Whenever a player moves, the previous position becomes a wall. 
  A wall blocks the shooting as well as the scope of movement.
- The point of the game is to move around the board without getting shot by the opponent
  or captured by the walls.
